PRETORIA - Almost 54 years later, and there is finally some hope for former residents of District Six. Land Reform Minister Thoko Didiza has submitted a detailed plan for its redevelopment as per a court order. The plan will see construction taking place in phases. READ: Land reform can deliver 'social cohesion': report Residents were forcefully removed from their homes by the apartheid government in 1966. Didiza said 60 days will be put aside for objections, but she hopes the community of Cape Town will support the people of District Six in the redevelopment "In terms of the development, we're planning to complete this process within three years," she said. Didiza said the government has been consulting with the claimants on the outline of the plan and how the development will go forward, in compliance with the court order.